  "notes": "Pali — canonical language of Theravāda Buddhism (c. 3rd c. BCE). Middle Indo-Aryan: simplifies Sanskrit consonant clusters (geminates instead of heteroorganic clusters), loses distinction between palatal sibilant ⟨ś⟩ and retroflex ⟨ṣ⟩ (both → /s/). Romanisation follows PTS/Velthuis convention.",
